    "citation": "Jovanovic 2013 23891703",
    "population": "N: 78 (Serbia) Age: 37.62 (19-67) WT: 75.19 (46-113)",
    "model_type": "PK",
    "objective": "“to evaluate the influence of demographic, biochemical parameters and treatment characteristics of patients on the PK variability of TPM”",
    "covariates": "Tested: gender, TOB, co-therapy with LTG, LEV, VPA, CBZ, BDZ and RIS; WT, age, renal function (MDRD), liver enzymes (AST, ALP, CHO), BIL, ALB, PRO, dose of CBZ, VPA, LTG and LEV. Included: DCBZ and MDRD on CL/F and WT on V/F",
    "observations": "A one-compartment model with first order absorption and elimination was used to fit the concentrationtime TPM data. Volume of distribution of TPM was estimated at 0.575 l/kg. Daily carbamazepine dose (DCBZ) and renal function estimated by Modification of diet in renal disease (MDRD) formula significantly influenced CL/F. Mean TPM CL/F during CBZ co-therapy was 2.46 l/h (increase of 60.8%).",
    "dose": "Steady-state oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "1-compartment model with first order absorption and elimination",
    "equations": "CL/F = theta1*(1+theta2*DCBZ/1000)*exp(theta3*(MDRD-95.72))*exp(eta1) V/F = theta4*WT Ka = theta5 Cobs = Cipred*(1+eps1) Notes: based on literature data, Ka was fixed to 2 h-1 due to limited data collected during absorption phase",
    "parameter_values": "Theta1 = 1.53 Theta2 = 0.476 Theta3 = 0.00476 Theta4 = 0.575 Theta5 = 2 Omega1 = 0.027 Sigma1 = 0.134",
    "validation": "Yes (Bootstrap 1000 samples; pcPVC, NPC) / No"
  },
